{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018vCyk9h5vFB8MHRCHLkSWN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue clearly now. The task wants `VEGETABLES` to merge with `LEMON HERB ROASTED`, but the existing test says `INGREDIENTS` should NOT merge with `WORD ONE`.\n\nThe distinction is:\n- `INGREDIENTS`, `DIRECTIONS`, `INSTRUCTIONS`, `METHOD`, `PREPARATION`, `STEPS` are structural/process labels that mark the beginning of a recipe section — these should NEVER merge into a title\n- `VEGETABLES`, `SEAFOOD`, `FISH`, `SOUPS`, `SALADS`, `DESSERTS`, etc. are food category/chapter labels that could be part of a recipe title (e.g., \"LEMON HERB ROASTED VEGETABLES\")\n\n\nSo my approach should be to define a set of structural section labels that are never allowed to merge, while allowing food category labels to merge with preceding text.\n\nI'm creating a helper function that checks whether a section label is structural versus a food category, then using that to control the merge behavior. I'll need to include both English and Polish structural labels in this set.\n\nDefining the structural labels set... I'm realizing the core issue is distinguishing between structural labels like \"INGREDIENTS\" or \"DIRECTIONS\" that shouldn't merge, versus food category labels like \"VEGETABLES\" that can appear within a title. Rather than building complex validation logic, I could create a separate set of strict structural labels and only block merging for those, letting food categories merge naturally. continuing to flesh out the structural versus category distinction. The structural labels are the ones that should never merge—things like ingredients, directions, method, preparation, and their Polish equivalents. The category labels like vegetables, seafood, and desserts are different because they could legitimately appear in recipe titles, so I should allow those to merge with preceding text. This means my merge condition only needs to check against the structural subset, not the full set of section labels.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1197,"cache_read_input_tokens":27871,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1197},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6746208e-9db7-45b5-89d0-a33b9f6b28a6","uuid":"83cd761c-9f47-4c3d-8ae4-eb3985f2ed5f"}
