{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01DcKxRT4J3uhgHuAUKNDfin","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The fix needs to distinguish between structural section labels (ingredients, directions, etc.) and food category labels (vegetables, fish, etc.). Let me implement this properly.\n\nThe approach:\n1. Create a `STRUCTURAL_SECTION_LABELS` set with just the process/structural labels\n2. The merge condition relaxation: allow merging if the next word is a food category label (not a structural one) when preceded by a short 2-4 word fragment\n\nActually, I realize the simplest approach is to check if the label is only in the \"chapter/category labels\" part of SECTION_LABELS but not in the \"structural\" part. Let me create two sets.\n\n\nI'm thinking the minimal fix would be to define a strict set of structural labels that always act as hard breaks, preventing short fragments from merging into them even when the relaxation logic would normally allow it.\n\nDefining strict section labels... I need to create a helper function that applies the same normalization logic as `isSectionLabel` so I can consistently check against the strict labels set. This way both the general section label check and the strict structural label check use identical normalization, avoiding any mismatches between how text is processed. I'm reconsidering whether I really need a separate function for this. The core distinction I'm trying to make is between food type labels like `VEGETABLES` and process-oriented labels like `INGREDIENTS` — but adding another helper function and set might be overcomplicating things when I could just refine the existing logic to handle both cases more elegantly. The safest approach is to define a set of structural section labels that act as hard blocks to prevent merging—this way I can handle both the pattern matching for recipe titles like \"LEMON HERB ROASTED VEGETABLES\" while still blocking cases like \"WORD ONE INGREDIENTS\". Let me examine the current code to see exactly what needs to change.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1491,"cache_read_input_tokens":29068,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1491},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6746208e-9db7-45b5-89d0-a33b9f6b28a6","uuid":"eb0d279d-dc8b-4e1b-bfd6-a4f824180875"}
